---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { SITE_TITLE, SITE_DESCRIPTION } from '../consts';
import mycorrhizaeImage from '/public/mycojmo-index-hdr.png';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main class="index-page">
			<Image src={mycorrhizaeImage} alt="Mycorrhizae" loading="eager" />
			<hr>
			<h1>Justin Moore</h1>
			<h2>Head of Technology | Engineering Leader | PhD Astrophysicist → Bitcoin Infrastructure Architect</h2>

			<p>
				I went from managing robotic telescopes across 3 continents to leading 30+ engineers
				building secure Bitcoin multisig collaborative custody infrastructure. I bring scientific rigor with startup velocity.
			</p>

			<h3>What I've Led:</h3>

			<h4>Team Leadership & Crisis Management</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>Led 30+ engineer organization across Mobile, Data, Infrastructure, DevOps, QA, and Product teams</li>
				<li>Took over post-RIF: management responsibility changed overnight from 0 → 18 engineers</li>
				<li>Scaled team 3x while improving delivery from bi-weekly → weekly → daily production releases</li>
				<li>Built Unchained University, Proving Grounds, and Internal Navigator onboarding programs</li>
			</ul>

			<h4>Infrastructure & Cost Optimization</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>Cut AWS infrastructure costs by 40% while migrating to Kubernetes (EKS)</li>
				<li>Passed SOC 2 Type II audit on first attempt</li>
				<li>Maintained zero-downtime operations for Bitcoin custody systems (money can't wait)</li>
				<li>Migrated from Ansible + EC2 to containerized infrastructure with custom Helm charts</li>
			</ul>

			<h4>Systems at Scale</h4>
			<ul>
				<li>Managed distributed robotic telescope network spanning 3 continents (PhD work)</li>
				<li>Built and shipped automation reducing manual effort by 90% (DocuSign integration)</li>
				<li>Designed and operated systems handling Bitcoin custody and trading at scale</li>
				<li>Built custom hardware + software for astronomical research (custom polarimeter for GRBs)</li>
			</ul>

			<p>
				<strong>Technologies:</strong> Python, Kubernetes, AWS, React, Flask, Bitcoin protocol, Terraform,
				Helm, Jenkins, PostgreSQL, Redis | <strong>Certified:</strong> CKA (Kubernetes Administrator, 2024)
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>What I Bring</h2>

			<h3>Pattern Recognition Across Complex Systems</h3>
			<p>
				I've debugged Kubernetes networking issues, designed Bitcoin custody architecture,
				and managed telescope networks observing one-time astronomical events. When your
				team is stuck, I can usually identify the root cause quickly—not because I'm
				smarter, but because I've debugged this category of problem many times before.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Recent example:</strong> Led post-RIF recovery, scaled team 3x, shipped daily releases,
				and cut AWS costs 40% simultaneously.
			</p>

			<h3>Thriving in High-Stakes, Low-Information Environments</h3>
			<p>
				Give me a crisis situation with unclear root cause, an unfamiliar codebase with
				no documentation, or a new cloud platform I've never used. I'm energized by what
				makes others anxious.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>War story:</strong> Management responsibility changed overnight 0→18 engineers post-RIF.
				Team recovered within 6 months, scaled to 30+ within 18 months, with zero
				regrettable attrition.
			</p>

			<h3>Building High-Performing Teams</h3>
			<p>
				I don't just architect systems—I build teams that ship. Created comprehensive
				onboarding programs (Unchained University, Proving Grounds) that reduced
				ramp-up time from 3 months to 3 weeks.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Track record:</strong> Led teams from 5 to 30+ engineers, established coding standards
				and review processes, coached multiple engineers into leadership roles.
			</p>

			<h3>Full-Stack Thinking (Literally)</h3>
			<p>
				PhD-trained to think deeply about complex systems. Can debug from hardware
				(PCBs, networking) through cloud infrastructure (Kubernetes, AWS) to business
				impact (cost optimization, delivery predictability).
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Unique background:</strong> Built custom scientific instrumentation → managed
				multi-continent distributed systems → led Bitcoin infrastructure teams. I bring
				patterns from all three worlds.
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>My Ideal Scenarios</h2>

			<p><strong>Chaos → Order → Knowledge Transfer → Next Challenge</strong></p>

			<p>I specialize in:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>Post-crisis team recovery and scaling</li>
				<li>Infrastructure modernization and cost optimization</li>
				<li>Shipping in regulated/high-stakes environments (SOC 2, Bitcoin custody)</li>
				<li>Building teams and culture from scratch or rebuilding after disruption</li>
				<li>Embedded leadership for high-impact technical initiatives</li>
			</ul>

			<p><strong>Not my sweet spot:</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Long-term maintenance of stable systems (I'll get bored, you'll get diminishing returns)</li>
				<li>Pure HR/organizational design across departments</li>
				<li>Vendor management and procurement negotiations</li>
			</ul>

			<hr>

			<h2>How I Work</h2>

			<p>
				<strong>Short to medium-term embedded engagements</strong> (2 weeks to 12 months). I become
				part of your team, understand the problem deeply, and work alongside you to solve it.
			</p>

			<p>
				<strong>My guarantee:</strong> If after the first week you don't see clear value, I'll refund
				the engagement. In my career, I've never had to do this.
			</p>

			<p><strong>What success looks like:</strong></p>
			<ul>
				<li>Team is unblocked and shipping</li>
				<li>Infrastructure costs optimized</li>
				<li>Delivery predictability improved</li>
				<li>Knowledge transferred, not hoarded</li>
				<li>You're set up to continue without me</li>
			</ul>

			<hr>

			<h2>Let's Talk</h2>

			<p>
				<strong>For CTOs, VPs of Engineering, Founders:</strong><br>
				Need someone to embed with your team for a high-stakes project, turn around a
				stuck initiative, or bring technical leadership during growth/crisis?
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:work@mycojmo.com">work@mycojmo.com</a>
			</p>

			<p>
				<strong>For Technical Conversations:</strong><br>
				Want to talk about interesting problems, distributed systems, Bitcoin infrastructure,
				or Kubernetes architecture?
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:play@mycojmo.com">play@mycojmo.com</a>
			</p>

			<hr>

			<p>
				<strong>Credentials:</strong><br>
				<a href="https://justinpmoore.com/jmo-v2025-09-04.pdf" target="_blank">Download Full CV</a> |
				<a href="https://linkedin.com/in/justinpewittmoore" target="_blank">LinkedIn</a> |
				<a href="https://github.com/mycojmo" target="_blank">GitHub</a>
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>Why the name?</h2>

			<p>
				The word "Myco" relates to fungi and their mycorrhizal networks—underground
				symbiotic connections that help forests thrive. Like mycorrhizae, I embed with
				organizations to enable growth through collaborative problem-solving.
			</p>
			<p>
				Plus, JMO is what people call me.
			</p>

			<hr>

			<h2>About the Parent Stuff</h2>

			<p>
				If you're looking for parenting help (specifically around managing when you or
				your partner is traveling), find me over here → <a href="https://pitd.io" target="_blank">pitd.io</a>
			</p>

			<hr>

			<p>
				<strong>Note:</strong> This is the consulting/fractional work site. For full-time leadership
				roles or co-founder opportunities, let's talk about what you're building and
				whether my background (PhD dropout → Bitcoin → engineering leadership) fits your needs.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
